@node Editor API --- Minor Modes
@chapter Editor API --- Minor Modes

@cindex minor modes
@cindex global minor modes

Minor modes are buffer-local feature modes.  Active global minor modes
apply to existing buffers and future buffers unless a buffer has an
explicit local override.

@deffn Function define-minor-mode name description @r{[}lighter global@r{]}
Register a minor mode.  This low-level helper records the mode name,
description, lighter, and whether it supports global activation.  Built
in T-Lisp mode files define the user-facing commands such as
@code{line-numbers-mode} and @code{global-line-numbers-mode}.
@end deffn

Generated mode commands follow the Emacs-style argument rule used by
the built-ins: no argument toggles, @code{t} or a positive number
enables, and @code{nil}, zero, or a negative number disables.

@deffn Function minor-mode-register name description @r{[}lighter@r{]}
Register or update a minor mode.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-set-keymap name keymap
Associate an existing T-Lisp keymap value with a minor mode.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-toggle name
Toggle @var{name} for the current buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-set name state
Enable or disable @var{name} for the current buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-active-p name
Return true when @var{name} is active in the current buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-list-active
Return active minor mode names for the current buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-list-all
Return all registered minor mode names.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-lighter name
Return @var{name}'s status-line lighter.
@end deffn

@deffn Function minor-mode-list-lighters
